# Onshape REST API edit

Change a Part Studio feature parameter over HTTPS and verify it persisted — no
browser, no 2FA, no bot detection. This is the **preferred** path; reach for
@onshape/playwright only for edits the API can't express or for visual checks.

## Model

- A document is addressed by `did/wid/eid` (document / **workspace** / element),
  read straight from the URL `…/documents/{did}/w/{wid}/e/{eid}`. POSTs target a
  workspace (`/w/`), never a version (`/v/`).
- A **Part Studio** holds the feature tree (sketches, extrudes…). To change a
  depth: `GET …/partstudios/d/{did}/w/{wid}/e/{eid}/features`, mutate the
  `expression` of the depth `BTMParameterQuantity-147`, then POST the full
  feature back to `…/features/featureid/{fid}` wrapped in a
  `BTFeatureDefinitionCall-1406`. Send the **whole** feature — omitted params reset.
- Verify by re-GETting features (read the expression back) and/or comparing
  `…/massproperties` volume before/after.

## Auth

API key pair from dev-portal.onshape.com (secret shown once). Two schemes:
**HTTP Basic** (`auth=(access, secret)` over HTTPS — "local testing only") and
**HMAC-SHA256 request signing** (production). The script signs with HMAC:
string-to-sign is `method, On-Nonce, Date, Content-Type, path, query` each
`\n`-terminated then lowercased; header is `Authorization: On <key>:HmacSHA256:<sig>`.

> The official `onshape-client` Python SDK is archived (frozen 2021); the example
> uses raw `requests` instead. Base URL `https://cad.onshape.com`, version pinned
> in the path (`/api/v10/…`) — bare `/api/` falls back to ancient v0.

## Recipes

`self-test` runs the full edit+verify flow against an in-process mock (no keys).
`edit` needs `ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY` + `ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY` and a Part Studio URL.

```just
# prove the edit+verify flow with no credentials (in-process mock of the features API)
self-test:
  python3 examples/onshape/onshape_edit.py --self-test

# change the first extrude's depth on a live doc; needs ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY/SECRET_KEY in env
edit url depth="50 mm":
  python3 examples/onshape/onshape_edit.py {{quote(url)}} {{quote(depth)}}
```
